
Overview of noun requirement

The noun requirement has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (19) requirement, demand -- (required activity; "the requirements of his work affected his health"; "there were many demands on his time")
2. (18) necessity, essential, requirement, requisite, necessary -- (anything indispensable; "food and shelter are necessities of life"; "the essentials of the good life"; "allow farmers to buy their requirements under favorable conditions"; "a place where the requisites of water fuel and fodder can be obtained")
3. (11) prerequisite, requirement -- (something that is required in advance; "Latin was a prerequisite for admission")
